{"id":477993,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denis_Mack_Smith","text":"e=\"preserve\">Denis Mack Smith CBE FBA FRSL (3 March 1920 \u2013 11 July 2017) was a British historian. He has written many books and articles on the history of Italy from the Risorgimento onwards. He wrote biographies of famous Italians in history: Giuseppe Garibaldi, Camillo Cavour, Victor Emmanuel II, and Benito Mussolini. He was born in London.\nCareer.\nBetween 1942 and 1945, Smith was an officer in the British War Cabinet. From 1947 to 1962 he was a fellow, tutor and lecturer at the University of Cambridge. From 1962 to 1987 he was a Senior Research Fellow at All Souls College, Oxford. He is an Honorary Fellow at Wolfson College, Oxford and of Peterhouse, Cambridge.\nSmith died on 11 July 2017 in London at the age of 97.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Order_of_the_British_Empire","surface_form":"CBE","offset":30},{"uri":"Fellow_of_the_British_Academy","surface_form":"FBA","offset":34},{"uri":"FRSL","surface_form":"FRSL","offset":38},{"uri":"Historian","surface_form":"historian","offset":87},{"uri":"Writer","surface_form":"written","offset":105},{"uri":"Book","surface_form":"book","offset":118},{"uri":"Article","surface_form":"article","offset":128},{"uri":"History","surface_form":"history","offset":144},{"uri":"Italy","surface_form":"Italy","offset":155},{"uri":"Risorgimento","surface_form":"Risorgimento","offset":170},{"uri":"Biography","surface_form":"biographies","offset":201},{"uri":"Italy","surface_form":"Italians","offset":223},{"uri":"Giuseppe_Garibaldi","surface_form":"Giuseppe Garibaldi","offset":244},{"uri":"Camillo_Benso%2C_Count_of_Cavour","surface_form":"Camillo Cavour","offset":264},{"uri":"Victor_Emmanuel_II_of_Italy","surface_form":"Victor Emmanuel II","offset":280},{"uri":"Benito_Mussolini","surface_form":"Benito Mussolini","offset":304},{"uri":"London","surface_form":"London","offset":337},{"uri":"Officer","surface_form":"officer","offset":